Who's News:
   General Electric Picks
   Two Vice Presidents
Thomas R. Brock, 46, was named vice president of GE
Industrial Systems and Services in Salem, Va. Mr. Brock,
whose post is newly created, had been general manager of GE
Drive Systems, also in Salem.
   GE Nuclear Energy, GE Meter and Control, GE Industrial
Systems and Services, and GE Industrial Systems and Services
are businesses of the GE Industrial and Power Systems, which
had 1991 revenue of $6.18 billion, accounting for
approximately 10% of GE's revenue.